1
00:00:55,958 --> 00:00:58,500
The locals here have believed
in spirits for ages.

2
00:00:59,541 --> 00:01:01,666
Maybe even before there was any religion.

3
00:01:09,000 --> 00:01:13,083
But the meaning of spirits for Isan people

4
00:01:13,166 --> 00:01:15,958
might not be the same as for most.

5
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:36,583
We believe everything
that goes beyond nature

6
00:01:37,291 --> 00:01:39,291
is all called spirits,

7
00:01:40,500 --> 00:01:43,291
not just the souls of dead people.

8
00:01:52,333 --> 00:01:55,500
We believe
spirits are in every single thing.

9
00:02:01,000 --> 00:02:02,291
In houses,

10
00:02:03,458 --> 00:02:05,291
in forests, in mountains,

11
00:02:09,791 --> 00:02:10,875
in trees,

12
00:02:12,666 --> 00:02:14,750
in rice fields.

13
00:02:15,541 --> 00:02:18,208
Every area has spirits. All of it.

14
00:02:22,166 --> 00:02:26,500
IN 2018, A DOCUMENTARY TEAM
TRAVELED ALL OVER THAILAND

15
00:02:26,583 --> 00:02:29,708
TO STUDY THE LIVES OF SHAMANS.

16
00:02:31,625 --> 00:02:34,791
AFTER INTERVIEWING MANY SHAMANS,

17
00:02:34,875 --> 00:02:38,583
THE TEAM DECIDED TO STUDY NIM'S LIFE.

18
00:02:40,541 --> 00:02:43,041
THE SHAMAN OF GODDESS BA YAN.

19
00:02:47,375 --> 00:02:50,375
For Isan people, spirits have many types

20
00:02:50,458 --> 00:02:54,000
such as Phee Fah, Phee Tan,

21
00:02:54,500 --> 00:02:57,166
Phee Chua, Phee Ban, Phee Muang,

22
00:02:57,250 --> 00:02:58,458
Phee Pop, and Phee Ka.

23
00:02:58,541 --> 00:02:59,458
They're all spirits.

24
00:03:00,458 --> 00:03:04,791
There are good spirits that protect us,

25
00:03:04,875 --> 00:03:06,625
and evil spirits

26
00:03:07,333 --> 00:03:11,333
that haunt us and make us sick.

27
00:03:11,833 --> 00:03:13,458
And the spirit within you, who is it?

28
00:03:15,166 --> 00:03:17,083
Let me say it in central dialect.

29
00:03:17,625 --> 00:03:20,333
They call it "possessing."

30
00:03:21,083 --> 00:03:23,000
In Isan, they call it Ma Tiam.

31
00:03:24,041 --> 00:03:27,333
I'm the shaman for Goddess Ba Yan.

32
00:04:09,916 --> 00:04:12,250
Ba Yan is an ancestral spirit.

33
00:04:12,750 --> 00:04:14,583
She's a good spirit

34
00:04:14,666 --> 00:04:18,375
who has protected the villages
for a long time.

35
00:04:20,916 --> 00:04:24,625
Actually, no one knows
who She is or where She's from.

36
00:04:24,708 --> 00:04:27,708
But they've paid respect to Her
for many generations.

37
00:04:36,666 --> 00:04:39,583
SHAMAN BLOODLINE

38
00:04:39,666 --> 00:04:43,708
A DOCUMENTARY ABOUT THE SHAMAN
INHERITANCE IN A FAMILY.

39
00:04:43,791 --> 00:04:49,666
My family has been Ba Yan's shaman
for many generations.

40
00:04:49,750 --> 00:04:51,375
Ever since I was born,

41
00:04:51,458 --> 00:04:53,458
I saw my grandmother as Her medium.

42
00:04:53,541 --> 00:04:57,625
Ba Yan only chooses women
to be Her medium.

43
00:04:58,125 --> 00:05:01,041
Lots of locals would come to see us.

44
00:05:01,708 --> 00:05:05,875
Every year we have a ceremony.
A very big one.

45
00:05:06,458 --> 00:05:08,500
The locals will ask

46
00:05:08,583 --> 00:05:11,500
how the village
will fare for the coming year.

47
00:05:11,583 --> 00:05:14,125
After my grandmother died,

48
00:05:15,208 --> 00:05:18,500
the next person to inherit Ba Yan
was my aunt.

49
00:05:20,208 --> 00:05:26,083
After my aunt, the next shaman
was supposed to be Noi, my elder sister,

50
00:05:27,833 --> 00:05:30,250
but Noi declined the inheritance.

51
00:05:30,333 --> 00:05:32,750
Ba Yan then chose…

52
00:05:33,875 --> 00:05:35,958
me instead.

53
00:05:40,083 --> 00:05:44,583
Don't shamans have to shake their bodies
or change their voices?

54
00:05:44,666 --> 00:05:46,375
You might have watched too much TV.

55
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:48,750
It doesn't have to be like that.

56
00:05:49,333 --> 00:05:53,875
As you've seen,
people come and see me every day.

57
00:05:53,958 --> 00:05:56,416
Some come to heal their sickness.

58
00:05:56,500 --> 00:05:59,875
Some ask for blessings or wishes.

59
00:06:00,666 --> 00:06:01,875
Some repay their wishes

60
00:06:01,958 --> 00:06:04,708
with offerings of a jar of liquor
and a chicken.

61
00:06:05,666 --> 00:06:07,041
Tell me what happened?

62
00:06:07,125 --> 00:06:09,958
My husband found this cobra
and made liquor out of it.

63
00:06:10,041 --> 00:06:11,750
I told him not to drink it, but he did.

64
00:06:11,833 --> 00:06:14,375
His arms and legs went numb.
He doesn't have any strength.

65
00:06:15,041 --> 00:06:16,791
Where did you get it from?

66
00:06:16,875 --> 00:06:19,166
I got it from the cemetery.

67
00:06:19,250 --> 00:06:22,708
This is the cause of your misery,
paying for your bad karma.

68
00:06:22,791 --> 00:06:26,166
Because you've drunk the soul
that resided in this animal.

69
00:06:35,583 --> 00:06:37,625
Can you treat every illness?

70
00:06:37,708 --> 00:06:40,041
If someone has cancer
and they come to see me…

71
00:06:41,208 --> 00:06:42,458
they will die for sure.

72
00:06:45,583 --> 00:06:49,958
I can only treat illnesses
that happen from the unseen

73
00:06:50,041 --> 00:06:51,875
such as black magic,

74
00:06:51,958 --> 00:06:55,375
or if a spirit has harmed you,
I can cure it.

75
00:06:55,458 --> 00:06:58,583
But if it's a normal illness,
I advise you to go see a doctor.

76
00:08:01,750 --> 00:08:06,416
I never thought of being a shaman before.
Actually, I didn't want to be one.

77
00:08:06,500 --> 00:08:10,166
There was a period when I was always sick.

78
00:08:10,250 --> 00:08:14,416
No matter what, I couldn't get better.
It was so painful

79
00:08:14,500 --> 00:08:19,458
to the point that I wanted to run away,
to get away from it all.

80
00:08:19,541 --> 00:08:21,083
Why does it have to be me?

81
00:08:21,166 --> 00:08:22,208
But I didn't succeed.

82
00:08:22,291 --> 00:08:25,916
So I agreed to let Her take me.
Actually, it is great.

83
00:08:26,000 --> 00:08:29,083
Now I get to pray every day
and do ceremonies.

84
00:08:29,166 --> 00:08:33,958
And people come to see me,
asking for help when they have troubles.

85
00:08:35,791 --> 00:08:37,875
Now I consider it to be really good.

86
00:08:39,375 --> 00:08:40,458
I'm at ease.

87
00:08:40,541 --> 00:08:42,833
I can't even remember
why I first didn't accept Her,

88
00:08:42,916 --> 00:08:44,125
why I was mad at Her.

89
00:08:54,250 --> 00:08:58,083
SEAMSTRESS

90
00:09:25,666 --> 00:09:29,250
We're going to Wiroj's funeral. Who is he?

91
00:09:29,333 --> 00:09:31,041
Wiroj is…

92
00:09:32,791 --> 00:09:36,333
the husband of my elder sister, Noi.

93
00:09:36,416 --> 00:09:39,541
He found out last year that he had cancer.

94
00:09:39,625 --> 00:09:40,916
I'm sorry for your loss.

95
00:09:41,666 --> 00:09:46,000
I don't know why
all the men in the Yasantia family

96
00:09:46,083 --> 00:09:47,750
die under bad circumstances.

97
00:09:48,666 --> 00:09:53,250
Wiroj's grandfather was stoned
to death by laborers.

98
00:09:54,125 --> 00:09:57,458
Wiroj's dad,
when his factory went belly-up,

99
00:09:57,541 --> 00:09:59,583
he burned the factory for insurance money.

100
00:10:00,208 --> 00:10:03,666
When he was caught,
he poisoned himself to death.

101
00:10:03,750 --> 00:10:06,125
As for Mac, Wiroj's eldest son,

102
00:10:07,791 --> 00:10:09,791
he died in a motorcycle accident
several years ago.

103
00:10:11,666 --> 00:10:12,500
Huh?

104
00:10:33,666 --> 00:10:34,750
How have you been?

105
00:10:35,250 --> 00:10:39,041
I haven't seen you for so long.
Have you forgotten your family?

106
00:10:39,125 --> 00:10:41,625
If no one died, we'd never see each other.

107
00:10:41,708 --> 00:10:44,416
-Is this tray ready?
-Yeah, you can take it inside.

108
00:10:45,791 --> 00:10:49,750
-You always forget your relatives.
-Can you stop nagging?

109
00:10:54,958 --> 00:10:57,125
He's the pastor
from the church Noi goes to.

110
00:10:57,958 --> 00:10:59,500
Thank you for coming.

111
00:11:01,208 --> 00:11:04,333
Mink, please get a chair for the pastor.

112
00:11:12,916 --> 00:11:14,083
Mink.

113
00:11:14,166 --> 00:11:15,291
How are you?

114
00:11:15,375 --> 00:11:19,083
Your mom told me
you were the first one to find his body.

115
00:11:19,166 --> 00:11:20,291
I'm okay.

116
00:11:25,041 --> 00:11:28,750
My family has three siblings.

117
00:11:28,833 --> 00:11:30,291
There's Manit, the eldest.

118
00:11:30,916 --> 00:11:33,625
If you smoke a lot,
you can't tell one thing from another.

119
00:11:33,708 --> 00:11:36,750
Water? Want some water?

120
00:11:36,833 --> 00:11:38,958
Noi is the middle child,
and I'm the youngest.

121
00:11:39,583 --> 00:11:40,791
See…

122
00:11:40,875 --> 00:11:43,750
Wiroj, Noi's husband, just died.

123
00:11:44,291 --> 00:11:49,166
Before this, Mac, Noi's son, passed away.

124
00:11:49,791 --> 00:11:54,666
Now, Noi is left with Mink,
her only daughter.

125
00:11:55,500 --> 00:12:00,875
Actually,
Noi and Wiroj married a bit late.

126
00:12:00,958 --> 00:12:02,541
Once they married…

127
00:12:03,333 --> 00:12:07,541
Noi took over the dog meat shop
from her mother-in-law,

128
00:12:07,625 --> 00:12:09,875
Wiroj's mother.

129
00:12:10,833 --> 00:12:12,416
I don't know why she did that.

130
00:12:12,500 --> 00:12:14,750
The government doesn't allow it,
but Noi secretly does.

131
00:12:14,833 --> 00:12:17,541
My sisters,
they don't get along very well.

132
00:12:17,625 --> 00:12:23,041
They have had some kind of disagreement
ever since who knows when.

133
00:12:23,125 --> 00:12:29,333
I've tried to talk to them
to get them to reconcile, to make up.

134
00:12:30,041 --> 00:12:32,916
Come on. Go get your shoes.

135
00:12:33,000 --> 00:12:35,958
As if I would take anyone's shoes.

136
00:12:36,583 --> 00:12:38,125
-Thank you.
-My pleasure.

137
00:12:40,333 --> 00:12:41,333
Auntie.

138
00:12:43,666 --> 00:12:45,500
Mom wants you to get stuff from my house.

139
00:12:46,208 --> 00:12:49,083
She wrote it all down
and where everything is.

140
00:13:09,500 --> 00:13:10,541
Hello, Auntie Nim.

141
00:13:19,791 --> 00:13:20,625
Here.

142
00:13:21,291 --> 00:13:23,375
-Have you closed the door?
-Yes.

143
00:13:23,458 --> 00:13:25,875
-Lucky won't go outside, right?
-It won't.

144
00:13:27,458 --> 00:13:31,625
You brought the wrong cloth.
I wanted the thicker one.

145
00:13:31,708 --> 00:13:33,500
Why don't you go get it yourself then?

146
00:13:40,041 --> 00:13:41,708
Uncle, what the hell are you saying?

147
00:13:43,166 --> 00:13:44,875
No one said anything.

148
00:13:44,958 --> 00:13:46,958
-What the fuck did you say?
-Mink!

149
00:13:47,041 --> 00:13:48,416
I didn't say anything.

150
00:13:48,500 --> 00:13:51,375
Just mind your own business.
Are you talking shit about me?

151
00:13:52,291 --> 00:13:54,416
Who? No one said anything.

152
00:13:54,500 --> 00:13:56,208
-He cursed at me.
-I haven't done anything…

153
00:13:56,291 --> 00:13:57,375
You called me a whore!

154
00:13:57,458 --> 00:13:59,000
-Mink! Stop it!
-Hey!

155
00:13:59,083 --> 00:14:00,666
-Mink, don't!
-Damn you!

156
00:14:00,750 --> 00:14:03,541
-I didn't call you that!
-You just said it!

157
00:14:04,916 --> 00:14:06,416
Get him out of here, Mom!

158
00:14:06,500 --> 00:14:07,458
Mink, let's go.

159
00:14:07,541 --> 00:14:11,125
-Mink, go. Leave first.
-I'm not leaving. He cursed at me!

160
00:14:11,625 --> 00:14:14,125
No one said anything at all.

161
00:14:14,208 --> 00:14:17,875
-Dammit! Get out of here!
-Mink, calm down.

162
00:14:17,958 --> 00:14:20,958
-Mom, let go of me!
-Calm down, Mink.

163
00:14:22,416 --> 00:14:24,375
He cursed at me.

164
00:14:25,125 --> 00:14:26,500
He didn't.

165
00:14:26,583 --> 00:14:30,666
Does Mink usually drink a lot?

166
00:14:31,958 --> 00:14:34,583
I know she drinks,
but I didn't know it was this much.

167
00:14:35,083 --> 00:14:37,458
This is the first time
Mink's caused a scene.

168
00:14:37,541 --> 00:14:38,458
I see.

169
00:14:38,541 --> 00:14:39,541
Go ahead.

170
00:14:40,125 --> 00:14:41,125
See you around.

171
00:14:43,583 --> 00:14:44,708
Drive safely.

172
00:15:10,916 --> 00:15:11,916
Mink.

173
00:15:15,250 --> 00:15:16,250
Mink.

174
00:15:19,125 --> 00:15:20,125
Mink.

175
00:15:51,083 --> 00:15:52,125
Mink.

176
00:16:16,208 --> 00:16:17,416
Who died?

177
00:16:18,041 --> 00:16:20,333
The blind old woman
whose house is behind the temple.

178
00:16:21,833 --> 00:16:23,541
How did she die?

179
00:16:24,458 --> 00:16:25,541
I don't know.

180
00:16:49,625 --> 00:16:50,666
Mink.

181
00:16:52,041 --> 00:16:53,041
Mink!

182
00:17:27,541 --> 00:17:31,791
WIROJ YASANTIA

183
00:18:10,125 --> 00:18:11,333
Nim, what are you doing here?

184
00:18:16,500 --> 00:18:17,958
What are you doing in Mink's room?

185
00:18:19,166 --> 00:18:20,875
Why are you going through her things?

186
00:18:20,958 --> 00:18:24,625
I asked you a question.
Why don't you answer?

187
00:18:24,708 --> 00:18:26,541
Why aren't you saying anything? Gosh!

188
00:18:26,625 --> 00:18:28,833
What are you looking for? Tell me…

189
00:18:34,625 --> 00:18:35,666
Here.

190
00:18:36,416 --> 00:18:37,416
See?

191
00:18:40,208 --> 00:18:42,000
Do you know what this is?

192
00:18:42,083 --> 00:18:43,000
What?

193
00:18:44,416 --> 00:18:46,333
What are you doing? Both of you get out.

194
00:18:46,416 --> 00:18:48,708
-Mink, hold on.
-Mom, leave.

195
00:18:48,791 --> 00:18:50,291
Mink, you've started to have nightmares

196
00:18:50,375 --> 00:18:53,750
-and hear strange things, right?
-No! Nothing! Mom, get out.

197
00:18:53,833 --> 00:18:55,333
-Mink…
-Get out.

198
00:18:55,416 --> 00:18:56,541
Get out!

199
00:18:57,291 --> 00:18:59,000
Must you film everything, seriously?

200
00:19:06,375 --> 00:19:08,958
You know what the turmeric is for, right?

201
00:19:13,291 --> 00:19:16,250
You must tell me
if Mink shows any strange symptoms.

202
00:19:20,458 --> 00:19:21,291
Noi!

203
00:19:22,208 --> 00:19:25,000
I can take care of my child.
You should leave.

204
00:19:27,958 --> 00:19:31,208
What is it that Mink hangs in her closet?

205
00:19:31,291 --> 00:19:32,875
It's a turmeric called Pa Ta Ba.

206
00:19:32,958 --> 00:19:36,625
We believe it can protect us from spirits

207
00:19:36,708 --> 00:19:38,333
and other evil things.

208
00:19:40,583 --> 00:19:42,750
Why the hell did they come
into other people's rooms?

209
00:19:42,833 --> 00:19:45,833
They went through my stuff, too. Damn it!

210
00:19:45,916 --> 00:19:47,125
It's so freaking lame.

211
00:19:48,000 --> 00:19:49,250
Right?

212
00:19:51,916 --> 00:19:54,083
Why did you put the Pa Ta Ba in your room?

213
00:19:57,833 --> 00:20:01,083
What they did, it's so childish.
They're supposed to be the adults here.

214
00:20:04,125 --> 00:20:07,541
At the funeral the other day,
why were you staring at that blind lady?

215
00:20:09,000 --> 00:20:10,750
What blind lady?

216
00:20:19,625 --> 00:20:21,250
Do you see someone standing over there?

217
00:20:33,333 --> 00:20:34,250
Yes.

218
00:20:34,333 --> 00:20:35,791
I see someone there.

219
00:20:36,708 --> 00:20:37,916
Why?

220
00:20:47,583 --> 00:20:51,250
THE TEAM WENT OVER THE FOOTAGE

221
00:20:51,333 --> 00:20:54,583
AND FOUND MINK SHOWING
SOME STRANGE BEHAVIOR.

222
00:21:01,541 --> 00:21:03,958
What do Mink's recent symptoms mean?

223
00:21:06,666 --> 00:21:10,250
From what I've gathered,
they can be several things.

224
00:21:10,333 --> 00:21:13,791
Does that mean Ba Yan will move to Mink?

225
00:21:19,875 --> 00:21:20,958
I don't know.

226
00:21:23,708 --> 00:21:28,583
THE TEAM HAD AN IDEA.
IF A SHAMAN INHERITANCE IS REAL,

227
00:21:29,333 --> 00:21:34,125
THEY MIGHT BE ABLE
TO RECORD THE MANIFESTATION.

228
00:21:35,291 --> 00:21:39,708
THEY DECIDED TO FILM MINK
AND HER FAMILY, TOO.

229
00:21:48,416 --> 00:21:49,458
Hey.

230
00:21:49,541 --> 00:21:51,083
Are you going to film me all the time?

231
00:21:51,791 --> 00:21:53,000
Most of the time.

232
00:21:53,083 --> 00:21:55,166
Just make yourself comfortable.

233
00:21:57,708 --> 00:21:59,375
Tell me about your job.

234
00:21:59,458 --> 00:22:00,333
Sure.

235
00:22:00,916 --> 00:22:03,750
I work at the Recruitment Center.

236
00:22:03,833 --> 00:22:06,458
RECRUITMENT CENTER

237
00:22:06,541 --> 00:22:09,583
All day I assign work for people to do.

238
00:22:13,583 --> 00:22:14,958
NUMBER 13

239
00:22:15,041 --> 00:22:16,125
Number 6.

240
00:22:19,791 --> 00:22:20,916
Hello.

241
00:22:23,541 --> 00:22:26,208
I wake up at 5 a.m. I wake up early.

242
00:22:26,291 --> 00:22:29,208
I eat and get to work around 7, 8 a.m.

243
00:22:31,875 --> 00:22:34,583
In the afternoon there aren't many people.
So I have some free time.

244
00:22:34,666 --> 00:22:37,250
I'm not that tired with my work.

245
00:22:39,916 --> 00:22:41,250
And do you like your job?

246
00:22:41,333 --> 00:22:42,333
Yeah.

247
00:22:42,416 --> 00:22:45,416
I think I'm happy
helping others find jobs.

248
00:22:46,541 --> 00:22:47,666
Do you really mean it?

249
00:22:47,750 --> 00:22:49,875
Of course!
I sound like a beauty queen, huh?

250
00:22:51,166 --> 00:22:54,625
How do you feel towards people
who are shamans, like your aunt?

251
00:22:54,708 --> 00:22:55,625
Shamans?

252
00:22:57,000 --> 00:22:57,875
To be honest,

253
00:22:58,375 --> 00:23:00,333
I think it's nonsense.
I don't think it's real.

254
00:23:00,416 --> 00:23:02,458
Out of the blue, they make weird moves.

255
00:23:02,541 --> 00:23:05,125
Acting like Hanuman. It's so weird.

